page.title: 06WYNYARD GROVE
page.content: Wynyard Grove is on the edge of Bishop Auckland. There are lots of vehicles in our street especially parked cars. There are two or three old folks in the street who we don't see very often and one or two odd people. For instance the family across the road from us. The man comes out at about 10pm. and puts some carpet over his car engine covered with papers and at about 8am. he comes out and blows the tyres up with a footpump. All the houses in our street were built about 20 years ago and are semi-detached exept for the first one. Overall I like my house and street and would not like to move. Next to our house is an old railway line where I go for walks on sunny days. There is a field beside the line where I play football and cricket during the school holidays.
